People
Board
Chair,
Adviser
Named
for
Plymouth’s
Traxen
People
Board
Chair,
Adviser
Named
for
Plymouth’s
Traxen
By
Grace
Turner
-
October
29,
2020
177
Facebook
Twitter
Pinterest
WhatsApp
Mary
Petrovich
//
Photo
courtesy
of
Traxen
Mary
Petrovich
has
joined
Plymouth-based
Traxen’s
board
of
directors
as
chairman.
The
startup
focuses
on
trucking
technology.
Bill
Gryzenia
was
also
named
adviser
to
the
board.
“We
are
incredibly
pleased
to
have
Mary
and
Bill
playing
integral
roles
in
our
technology
company
as
we
cruise
forward
with
our
pilot
phase,”
says
Ali
Maleki,
founder
and
CEO.
“I
know
their
comprehensive
backgrounds
and
connectivity
to
the
industry
will
be
key
assets
to
Traxen’s
future
success.”
Petrovich
is
a
senior
executive
at
the
Carlyle
Group
and
chairman
of
DealerShop.
She
has
overseen
the
successful
private
equity
exits
of
three
companies
in
the
on-
and
off-highway
markets.
Previously,
she
served
as
executive
chairman
of
AxleTech,
where
she
helped
shape
the
company’s
electric
vehicle
strategy
for
the
truck
and
bus
markets.
She
is
also
former
president
of
Dura
Automotive’s
driver
controls
unit
and
served
in
roles
at
AlliedSignal,
Chrysler,
and
General
Motors
Co.
Boards
Petrovich
serves
on
include
United
Road,
Woodward
Inc.,
and
Xeeva
Software.
Gryzenia
serves
as
president
and
CEO
of
DealerShop.
He
has
expertise
in
advanced
driveline
technologies
and
was
previously
CEO
of
AxleTech,
vice
president
and
general
manager
of
Dana
Inc.’s
global
on-
and
off-highway
aftermarket
business,
director
of
business
development
with
Apexon,
and
Harnischfeger
Corp.
He
is
also
a
member
of
the
Syncreon
board.
“The
Traxen
team
has
worked
tirelessly
to
develop
amazing
technology
that
will
save
truck
fleets
millions
of
dollars
in
fuel
costs
upon
its
launch,”
says
Petrovich.
“I
look
forward
to
working
with
the
board
to
help
guide
Traxen
as
it
moves
to
commercialize
its
innovation
and
enters
a
strong
growth
phase.”
